\chapter{Tutorial Catalog}
\label{tutorial-catalog}

The tutorial definitions no longer live in Python code.  Instead, the
package reads one Markdown file per tutorial and turns those files into
the same in-memory [[Tutorial]] and [[TutorialStep]] objects that the
runner already understands.

That split keeps the authoring workflow simple.  Tutorial authors can
write ordinary Markdown with YAML front matter, while the runtime keeps a
small, typed model that the rest of the package can trust.


