\section{The loaded tutorial catalog}

The runner needs two operations from the catalog: list every available
tutorial and look up one tutorial by ID.  We therefore load the files up
front and keep both the ordered tuple and a direct lookup table.

<<classes>>=
class TutorialCatalog:
    """Load tutorial definitions from explicit Markdown paths."""

    <<tutorial catalog methods>>
@


\subsection{Initialising the catalog}

We resolve paths and parse files once during initialisation so the rest of
the package can treat the catalog as a stable snapshot.

<<tutorial catalog methods>>=
def __init__(self, tutorial_paths: tuple[str | Path, ...]):
    """Load tutorials from ``tutorial_paths``."""

    self.tutorial_paths = tuple(Path(path) for path in tutorial_paths)
    if self.tutorial_paths:
        self.files = resolve_tutorial_files(self.tutorial_paths)
        self.tutorials = tuple(load_tutorial_file(path) for path in self.files)
    else:
        self.files = ()
        self.tutorials = ()
    self.tutorials_by_id = {}
    for tutorial in self.tutorials:
        if tutorial.id in self.tutorials_by_id:
            raise ValueError(f"Duplicate tutorial ID {tutorial.id!r}.")
        self.tutorials_by_id[tutorial.id] = tutorial
