\section{Parsing the YAML front matter}

Each tutorial file starts with a front matter block delimited by
[[---]].  We separate that block from the Markdown body before doing any
further parsing so the step splitter never has to know about front matter.

<<functions>>=
def split_yaml_front_matter(text: str) -> tuple[str, str]:
    """Return ``(front_matter, body)`` for one tutorial file."""

    lines = text.splitlines(keepends=True)
    if not lines or lines[0].strip() != "---":
        raise ValueError(
            "Tutorial files must start with YAML front matter delimited by ---."
        )

    for index, line in enumerate(lines[1:], start=1):
        if line.strip() == "---":
            return "".join(lines[1:index]), "".join(lines[index + 1 :])

    raise ValueError("Tutorial front matter is missing its closing ---.")
@

<<test functions>>=
def test_split_yaml_front_matter_requires_delimiters():
    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match="YAML front matter"):
        split_yaml_front_matter("# Step\n\nDo it.\n")
@


\section{Reading top-level tutorial metadata}

The front matter must be a small YAML mapping.  We keep the schema narrow
so mistakes fail fast and tutorial authors can see exactly what the file
is expected to provide.

<<functions>>=
def front_matter_mapping(front_matter: str) -> dict:
    """Return the parsed YAML mapping for one tutorial front matter block."""

    payload = yaml.safe_load(front_matter) or {}
    if not isinstance(payload, dict):
        raise ValueError("Tutorial front matter must be a YAML mapping.")
    return payload
@


\section{Loading one tutorial file}

Loading a tutorial file is the point where the textual format becomes the
typed runtime model.

<<functions>>=
def load_tutorial_file(path: str | Path) -> Tutorial:
    """Load one Markdown tutorial file into a [[Tutorial]]."""

    tutorial_path = Path(path)
    text = tutorial_path.read_text()
    front_matter, body = split_yaml_front_matter(text)
    metadata = front_matter_mapping(front_matter)
    reject_unknown_keys(metadata, {"id", "title", "summary"}, "Tutorial")

    steps = tuple(
        build_tutorial_step(title, section_body)
        for title, section_body in split_step_sections(body)
    )
    return Tutorial(
        id=require_string(metadata, "id", "Tutorial"),
        title=require_string(metadata, "title", "Tutorial"),
        summary=require_string(metadata, "summary", "Tutorial"),
        steps=steps,
        source_path=str(tutorial_path.resolve()),
        source_digest=build_source_digest(text),
    )
@

