\section{Splitting the Markdown body into steps}

Each top-level heading begins a new tutorial step.  Lower-level headings
remain part of the step body, which lets tutorial authors keep ordinary
Markdown structure inside a step.

<<functions>>=
def split_step_sections(body: str) -> tuple[tuple[str, str], ...]:
    """Return ``(title, body)`` pairs for each top-level step heading."""

    sections = []
    title = None
    body_lines = []
    for line in body.splitlines():
        if line.startswith("# "):
            if title is not None:
                sections.append((title, "\n".join(body_lines).strip()))
            title = line[2:].strip()
            if not title:
                raise ValueError("Tutorial step headings must not be empty.")
            body_lines = []
            continue

        if title is None:
            if line.strip():
                raise ValueError(
                    "Tutorial body must begin with a top-level step heading."
                )
            continue

        body_lines.append(line)

    if title is None:
        raise ValueError("Tutorial files must define at least one step.")

    sections.append((title, "\n".join(body_lines).strip()))
    return tuple(sections)
@


\section{Optional per-step metadata blocks}

Most of the step body should stay ordinary Markdown.  Validation rules and
hints are the exception, so we reserve a small leading code fence with the
language tag [[tutorial-step]] for that metadata.

<<constants>>=
STEP_METADATA_FENCE = "```tutorial-step"
@

<<functions>>=
def step_metadata_and_instructions(section_body: str) -> tuple[dict, str]:
    """Return ``(metadata, instructions)`` for one step body."""

    stripped_body = section_body.strip()
    lines = stripped_body.splitlines()
    if not lines or lines[0].strip() != STEP_METADATA_FENCE:
        return {}, stripped_body

    for index, line in enumerate(lines[1:], start=1):
        if line.strip() == "```":
            metadata = yaml.safe_load("\n".join(lines[1:index])) or {}
            if not isinstance(metadata, dict):
                raise ValueError("Tutorial step metadata must be a YAML mapping.")
            instructions = "\n".join(lines[index + 1 :]).strip()
            return metadata, instructions

    raise ValueError("Tutorial step metadata is missing its closing ``` fence.")
@

\section{Building one tutorial step}

Once the optional metadata block is separated from the Markdown body, the
remaining conversion is a straightforward mapping onto [[TutorialStep]].

<<functions>>=
def build_tutorial_step(title: str, section_body: str) -> TutorialStep:
    """Build one tutorial step from a parsed Markdown section."""

    metadata, instructions = step_metadata_and_instructions(section_body)
    reject_unknown_keys(
        metadata,
        {"required_patterns", "check_command", "hint"},
        f"Step {title!r}",
    )
    if not instructions:
        raise ValueError(f"Step {title!r} must contain instructions.")

    return TutorialStep(
        title=title,
        instructions=instructions,
        required_patterns=string_tuple(
            metadata.get("required_patterns"),
            f"Step {title!r} required_patterns",
        ),
        check_command=optional_string(
            metadata.get("check_command"),
            f"Step {title!r} check_command",
        ),
        hint=optional_string(metadata.get("hint"), f"Step {title!r} hint"),
    )
@

